title: Which K-pop idols don't improve themselves much? - Quora

response.answer_text: Momo.  Now before you all hate me, let me explain. When Twice debuted with Ooh Ah, the Korean pronunciation of the non-Korean members werent… great. But it was still acceptable, since they just debuted and were young. The Korean public didn't say too much about that. Because like other non-Korean idols before, they knew they would become better. As they made comebacks, the pronunciation was getting better- except one person. Momo. After Yes or Yes, not just the Korean public, but the fans started to get annoyed. They left comments in the Melon asking Momo if she can improve her pronunciation like her bandmates. After More & More, the fans were done.  The most liked comment translates to: “Hello Momo-shi. We are not asking much from you. In order to work in Korea, then what is the number 1 required thing? It's Korean pronunciation. Your pronunciation has been an hot topic since debut, you haven't improved since. Honestly I was listening to the song and when I heard your singing, I was confused and didn't understand what you were saying so I immediately turned off the music. The fans are not asking much, we are not requiring great singing. We are just asking for pronunciation. Is it that hard? Korean pronunciation is one of the basics of being a KPOP idol.” The second liked comment translates to: “Is Momo's pronunciation real? Is she really a KPOP singer It's fucking funny" To summarize, the Korean fans are now just desperate for Momo's Korean pronunciation, which is one of the basics of being a KPOP idol. I have absolutely have NO intentions of dragging Momo down. She is a great idol, with awesome dancing and singing. It's just that if she masters her pronunciation, then she would become an even better idol.
